 a simple if-else/case to handle the wrap-around from 6 to 0.\n   - Initialize q to 4 to match the first observed value (though the waveform shows x at 0ns, the first valid state at 5ns is 4).\n\n3. Advice to avoid syntax errors:\n   - Ensure all ports match the specification exactly.\n   - Use 'logic' for all signals.\n   - Use 'always @(*)' for combinational logic and 'always @(posedge clk)' for sequential logic.\n   - Avoid 'unique' or 'inside' as per instructions.",
